Using a Raspberry Pi to control a Niles GXR2

Connect the wired connection of a raspberry pi to the expansion port on the Niles GXR2.  Connect the wireless network on the pi to your local area netork.
On a raspberry pi computer with apache properly configured, copy the following files from this directory into the /var/www/html directory:
index.html
getstatus.php
controller.php
niles.php
vol,php
nav.php

Use the ifconfig command to get the IP address of the wired connection.
From a computer on your local network, access enter the IP as the URL to access the web server.

You can control the Niles GXR2 from that web site.
